        <Grid x:Name="grdInst" Background="#CC000000" Grid.RowSpan="2" Visibility="Visible">
            <Grid x:Name="grdIntro" Margin="0,90,0,90">
                <Grid.Background>
                    <ImageBrush Stretch="UniformToFill" ImageSource="/Assets/Background.png"/>
                </Grid.Background>
                <TextBlock x:Name="InstTitle" Text="Introduction" FontSize="36" Margin="22,12,0,0" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Top" Foreground="White"/>
                <RichTextBox x:Name="Content1" TextAlignment="Justify" IsReadOnly="True" Margin="10,70,10,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontWeight="Light" FontSize="24" VerticalAlignment="Top" Visibility="Visible" Foreground="White">
                    <Paragraph>
                        Bulls and cows is a classic code-breaking puzzle game. It test and improve your memory and intelligence. It dates back several centuries as a paper and pencil game played between 2 players. Let us understand the rules.
                    </Paragraph>
                </RichTextBox>
                <RichTextBox x:Name="Content2" TextAlignment="Justify" IsReadOnly="True" Margin="10,70,10,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontWeight="Light" FontSize="24" VerticalAlignment="Top" Visibility="Collapsed" Foreground="White">
                    <Paragraph>
                        The code that you have to break is a 4 digit number. All digits of the number are different. And the number cannot start with 0. For example, the number can be 4390, 8743, 9012, etc. But it cannot be 0435, 4373, 6122, etc.
                    </Paragraph>
                </RichTextBox>
                <RichTextBox x:Name="Content3" TextAlignment="Justify" IsReadOnly="True" Margin="10,70,10,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontWeight="Light" FontSize="24" VerticalAlignment="Top" Visibility="Collapsed" Foreground="White">
                    <Paragraph>
                        You get 7 attempts for the challenge. And after each attempt, you will see the number of bulls and cows for that attempt. Bulls are the number of digits in your attempt that are at exact position as in the code. If code is 7234, then attempt 7530 contains two bulls.
                    </Paragraph>
                </RichTextBox>
                <RichTextBox x:Name="Content4" TextAlignment="Justify" IsReadOnly="True" Margin="10,70,10,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontWeight="Light" FontSize="24" VerticalAlignment="Top" Visibility="Collapsed" Foreground="White">
                    <Paragraph>
                        Cows are number of digits of code in your attempt at wrong position. If code is 7234, then attempt 7523 contains two cows. The aim of the game is to discover the four bulls. Let us understand the concept with help of examples.
                    </Paragraph>
                </RichTextBox>
                <Grid x:Name="Content5" Margin="10,70,10,0" Visibility="Collapsed">
                    <TextBlock x:Name="txtSuppose" Text="Click 'Generate' to load new sample" FontSize="24" FontWeight="Light" Margin="13,0,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="White"/>
                    <TextBlock Height="33" Margin="-73,40,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" Text="Code" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Width="230" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="24" TextAlignment="Center" Foreground="White"/>
                    <TextBlock Height="33" Margin="70,40,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" Text="Guess" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Width="230" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="24" TextAlignment="Center" Foreground="White"/>
                    <TextBlock Height="33" Margin="290,40,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" Text="Bulls &amp; Cows" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Width="140" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="24" TextAlignment="Center" Foreground="White"/>
                    <TextBlock x:Name="SampleCode" Text="5263" Height="53" Margin="12,75,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Width="100" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="36" TextAlignment="Left" Foreground="White"/>
                    <TextBlock x:Name="SampleAttempt" Text="5637" Height="53" Margin="147,75,0,0" Foreground="#FFAFAFAF" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Width="100" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="36" TextAlignment="Left"/>
                    <TextBlock x:Name="SampleBulls" Height="53" Text="1" Margin="290,75,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" Width="50" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="36" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextAlignment="Center" Foreground="#FFAFAFAF"/>
                    <TextBlock x:Name="SampleCows" Height="53" Text="2" Margin="380,75,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" Width="50" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="36" TextAlignment="Center" VerticalAlignment="Top" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Foreground="#FFAFAFAF"/>
                </Grid>
                <RichTextBox x:Name="Content6" TextAlignment="Justify" IsReadOnly="True" Margin="10,70,10,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" FontWeight="Light" FontSize="24" VerticalAlignment="Top" Visibility="Collapsed" Foreground="White">
                    <Paragraph>
                        The Analyzer is an optional feature for beginners of bulls and cows. It can be used to mark possibilities of digits occuring at different places. Users may use it the way it suits them. When they get a grip in Bulls and Cows, it is recommended not to use Analyzer.
                    </Paragraph>
                </RichTextBox>
                <Button x:Name="btnSkip" Content="Skip" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" HorizontalAlignment="Left" MinWidth="120" Margin="8,0,0,8" FontSize="24" Padding="15,10,15,10" Foreground="White"/>
                <Button x:Name="btnNewGen" Content="Generate" VerticalAlignment="Bottom" HorizontalAlignment="Left" MinWidth="120" Margin="115,0,0,8" FontSize="24" Padding="15,10,15,10" Visibility="Collapsed" Foreground="White"/>
